reviews.review_text: Brian, who just served us at 11:39pm on November 5th, was absolutely amazing. My family has lived by this McDonalds since it first opened in the early 2000s. The atmosphere here was less than amazing for quite some time but for a little while now I noticed a massive shift in the demeanor and friendliness of the workers. I understand this kind of job can be incredibly difficult and it can be really thankless. Some people are just horrible to service workers. I always try to respect that as much as I can. It takes a special kind of person to elevate the environment in a situation like that and Brian has done exactly that. I hope someone important sees this and ensures he receives the recognition he deserves.
Had a large order at a busy time and Caleb the Shift Leader this evening and another male manager in the back were controlling the entire restaurant very well. Great job everyone! Food
